OL,3,CBBC News ratings: something to brag
OL,4,Cabout
OL,6,GIn certain quarters, boastfulness is
OL,7,Gconsidered vulgar.
OL,9,FAnd the moment the BBC uses popularity
OL,10,Falone as a measure of success it is
OL,11,Fdoomed.
OL,13,FBut it's time for BBC marketing teams
OL,14,Fand press officers to take a lesson
OL,15,Ffrom Michael Grade in the eighties.
OL,17,FGrade cut out a headline from The Sun
OL,18,Fand pinned it to the wall. It read:
OL,19,F"If You've Got It Flaunt It."
OL,21,FAnd this is exactly what the BBC
OL,22,Fshould be doing.
